==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Gale
<hw>Gale</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>gagel</ets>, akin to D.
<ets>gagel</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the genus
<gen>Myrica</gen>, growing in wet places, and strongly resembling the
bayberry. The sweet gale (<spn>Myrica Gale</spn>) is found both in
Europe and in America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gale</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Gale
<hw>Gale</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Gabel</er>.]</ety> <def>The
payment of a rent or annuity.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Mozley &
W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gale day</b></col>, <cd>the day on which rent or interest
is due.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

